<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="13" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,306,871,897]" pageId="13" pageNumber="391">Remark:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zwick" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[314,594,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Perlodinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="391" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epiproctalis">
<emphasis box="[314,594,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="391">Perlodinella epiproctalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in most of the basin of Datong River, western Qilian Mountains (Qilian, Menyuan and Datong counties), and is also the only 
<taxonomicName box="[884,1111,907,933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis box="[884,1024,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="391">Perlodinella</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
known to emerge in this area during July and August.
</paragraph>
